OSOGBO – Barely twenty four hours to the National Convention of the ruling All Progressives Congress APC, the former Deputy Speaker, House of Representatives, Rt Honourable Lasun Yussuf, has tendered a letter of resignation of membership of APC. He tendered the letter few minutes ago at the state party secretariat along Ogo Oluwa, Gbongan Osogbo road. Yusuf contested the recently conducted governorship primary along with Governor Adegboyega Oyetola and former Secretary to Osun State Government, Alhaji Moshood Adeoti and came third after Oyetola and Adeoti. Yusuf had alleged during the primary of irregularities in the conduct of the governorship primary to favor Oyetola. He also kicked against the consensus arrangements for the ward and local government congresses of the party. He rejected the primary election which declared Oyetola as party candidate and had since stayed away from the party’s activities Details laters…